<br>
anyone have any idea if its prime only or it its both hands&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukellaen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kellaen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/21/02 1:02:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3952.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Call of Fire question about off hand proc</span><hr size=1> It's both, easy to test just ask any ranger. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umikaraz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mikaraz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/21/02 8:59:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3952.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Call of Fire question about off hand proc  </span><hr size=1> Yes, it will proc in your offhand, if your wielding a procing weapon as well it still have a chance to proc as well.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lythe>Lythe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/22/02 5:51:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3952.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Um</span><hr size=1> Imbue procs like Divine might,  call of fire, boon of the garou, instrument of nife etc... can appear to proc off anything,  kicks,  bashes, weapon hits etc...  The rate etc... is also independent of weapons (though does depend on dex).  (See Paladins of norrath for details if you like).<br>
<br>
What alledgedly happens is that - totally independently of your melee -  you roll for procs until you succeed on &quot;some clock&quot;.  It resets, starts rolling again and attaches a proc to sync with your next attack. (Originally when divine might came in,  they apparently just went off when you made the roll,  without even syncing to a swing or necessarily being in melee range (just with autoattack on) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .)<br>
<br>
So,  in summary,  spell proc imbues are *meant* to be completely independent of what you're weilding.  Fast 1hander(s) or slow 2hander,  it will end up going off at the same rate.  Or so the pallies say (and from my experience with Instrument of nife on my pally and garou/imp on my monk (similar rate using 2hander as 2 fast 1handers), I'd have to agree). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umurgatroyde.showPublicProfile?language=EN>murgatroyde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/22/02 4:31:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3952.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Um</span><hr size=1> I have yet to see an offhand proc.  Ran a test with GM Smith Hammer mainhand (not a weapon) and Bloodfrenzy off.  No proc for 10 minutes.<br>
<br>
I believe Sean from FoH also ran a test a while back and came to the same conclusion.<br>
<br>
